==English==
*see also [[gypsy]]

===Etymology===
From [[w:Old English language|Old English]][[category:Old English derivations]] [[Gypcyan]], [[w:French language|French]][[category:French derivations]] [[gyptien]] (meaning [[Egyptian]]), from [[w:Latin|Latin]][[Category:Latin derivations]] [[Aegyptius]]. See [[Egyptian]]. 

===Noun===
{{en-noun|Gypsy|Gypsies}}
# A member of the [[Roma]]. This term is considered pejorative by many and by the Roma themselves.
# One of a stateless people, whose communities, traditionally thought to have originally from India, entered Europe in 14th or 15th century, and are now widely distributed over Europe, Russia, Turkey, the Americas. 

